Distribution. Known only from the type locality, an area of rich species diversity. The Estación Científica Las Joyas is located within the Manantlán-Las Joyas Zone in the Reserva de la Biosfera de Manantlán. Las Joyas occupies an area of 1245 ha; the topography is irregular, and the altitude ranges from 1560 m to 2240 m (
Cuevas 1994
). According to Victor H. Toledo (personal communication), the vegetation at the station is cloud forest, with some trees reaching 40 m in height.
